---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Compare Credit Cards - TrueCred Loan Expert | Side-by-Side Card Comparison">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="/pages/credit-cards">Credit Cards</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Compare Credit Cards</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Compare Credit Cards</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Make an informed decision by comparing credit cards side-by-side. View features, fees, rewards, and benefits across 50+ cards from India's top banks in one comprehensive comparison matrix.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-columns"></i> Side-by-Side View
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-table-cells"></i> Feature Matrix
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-credit-card"></i> 50+ Cards
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <div class="content-main">

          <h2>Compare Credit Cards Side-by-Side</h2>
          <p>Selecting the right credit card requires careful comparison of multiple factors — annual fees, reward rates, welcome bonuses, lounge access, interest rates, and more. Our comparison tool lets you evaluate cards across all these parameters in a single view, so you can identify the card that delivers maximum value for your specific spending pattern.</p>
          <p>Below is a snapshot comparison of popular credit cards across different categories. Use the filters and detailed comparison features to narrow down your choice based on what matters most to you.</p>

          <h2>Why Compare Before Applying</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Avoid Hidden Charges:</strong> Compare joining fees, annual fees, interest rates, and late payment penalties across cards</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Maximise Reward Value:</strong> Different cards offer different reward structures — find the one that matches your spending categories</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Identify Best Perks:</strong> Compare lounge access, insurance coverage, concierge services, and milestone benefits</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Understand Fee Waivers:</strong> Many cards waive annual fees on meeting spending thresholds — compare these conditions</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Check Forex Charges:</strong> International spenders can save thousands by comparing forex markup rates across cards</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Make Informed Decisions:</strong> Reduce the risk of card regret by thoroughly comparing features before committing</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Popular Credit Cards — Feature Comparison</h2>
          <p>Here's a detailed comparison of five popular cards spanning different categories:</p>

          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Card Name</th>
                <th>Annual Fee</th>
                <th>Reward Rate</th>
                <th>Key Benefits</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>HDFC Regalia</strong></td>
                <td>₹2,500 (waived at ₹3L spend)</td>
                <td>4 RP per ₹150</td>
                <td>Lounge access, travel insurance, milestone bonus</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>ICICI Amazon Pay</strong></td>
                <td>Nil (Lifetime Free)</td>
                <td>5% for Prime, 3% Amazon</td>
                <td>No fee ever, instant cashback, wide acceptance</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Axis Flipkart</strong></td>
                <td>₹500 (waived at ₹2L spend)</td>
                <td>5% Flipkart, 4% preferred</td>
                <td>Cashback on Flipkart, Myntra, Cleartrip</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>SBI SimplyCLICK</strong></td>
                <td>₹499</td>
                <td>10X on partners, 5X online</td>
                <td>Amazon voucher welcome gift, fuel surcharge waiver</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>IndusInd Tiger</strong></td>
                <td>Nil (Lifetime Free)</td>
                <td>1.5% cashback</td>
                <td>Unlimited cashback, no minimum spend, free forever</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h2>What to Compare in Credit Cards</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Annual & Joining Fee:</strong> Check if the fee is justified by benefits; look for fee waiver conditions and lifetime free options</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Reward Structure:</strong> Compare earn rates, bonus categories, milestone rewards, and redemption value per point</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Interest Rate (APR):</strong> If you carry a balance, the interest rate matters — compare rates from 24% to 42% p.a. across issuers</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Welcome Benefits:</strong> Some cards offer welcome vouchers worth ₹500-₹10,000 on card activation and first spend</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Add-On Perks:</strong> Compare lounge access count, insurance coverage, concierge services, and fuel surcharge waivers</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit Limit:</strong> Higher-income thresholds typically mean higher limits, but compare actual limits offered by banks</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Use Our Comparison Tool</h3>
          <p>Follow these steps to compare credit cards on TrueCred:</p>

          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Select Cards</h4>
              <p>Choose up to 3 credit cards you want to compare from our database of 50+ options</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>View Comparison</h4>
              <p>See a detailed side-by-side breakdown of fees, rewards, perks, and eligibility</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Read Expert Verdict</h4>
              <p>Check our editor's pick and expert recommendations based on your spending profile</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Apply for the Best</h4>
              <p>Click apply on your chosen card and complete the digital application in minutes</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-alt" style="color: var(--primary); margin-right: 8px;"></i> Get Recommendations</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input">
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Monthly Income</option>
                  <option value="below-15k">Below ₹15,000</option>
                  <option value="15k-25k">₹15,000 - ₹25,000</option>
                  <option value="25k-50k">₹25,000 - ₹50,000</option>
                  <option value="50k-1l">₹50,000 - ₹1,00,000</option>
                  <option value="above-1l">Above ₹1,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input">
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Employment Type</option>
                  <option value="salaried">Salaried</option>
                  <option value="self-employed">Self Employed</option>
                  <option value="business">Business Owner</option>
                  <option value="student">Student</option>
                  <option value="freelancer">Freelancer</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                <i class="fas fa-paper-plane"></i> Get Recommendations
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/best-credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Best Credit Cards 2026</a>
              <a href="/pages/rewards-credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Rewards Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/cashback-credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Cashback Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/travel-credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Travel Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/fuel-credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Fuel Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/lifetime-free-credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Lifetime Free Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-card-eligibility"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Credit Card Eligibility</a>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQs</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Common questions about comparing credit cards</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What factors should I compare when choosing a credit card?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              The most important factors to compare are: (1) Annual fee and fee waiver conditions, (2) Reward earn rate and how much each point is worth, (3) Welcome bonuses and milestone rewards, (4) Interest rate on revolving credit, (5) Complimentary benefits like lounge access and insurance, (6) Forex markup if you make international transactions, (7) Fuel surcharge waiver percentage and cap, (8) Spending categories that earn accelerated rewards. Prioritise factors based on your primary use case — rewards for spenders, travel perks for travellers, or low fees for budget-conscious users.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How many credit cards can I compare at once?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              On TrueCred's comparison tool, you can compare up to 3 credit cards side-by-side in a single view. This keeps the comparison clean and easy to read. If you want to evaluate more cards, you can swap out any card in the comparison and replace it with another from our database of 50+ cards. We recommend first shortlisting 5-6 cards based on your priorities, then doing 2-3 comparison rounds to find your ideal card.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Is it bad to apply for multiple credit cards?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Applying for multiple cards in a short period can temporarily hurt your CIBIL score, as each application triggers a hard inquiry (reducing your score by 5-10 points each). It can also signal financial distress to lenders. We recommend comparing cards thoroughly using tools like ours, then applying for only 1-2 cards you're most likely to be approved for. Space out applications by at least 3-6 months. If you already hold 3+ cards, consider whether a new card truly adds value before applying.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Should I choose a card based on rewards or low fees?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              It depends on your annual spending. If you spend ₹5 lakh or more per year, a rewards-focused card (even with an annual fee) will likely deliver more value through reward points, cashback, and premium perks than a free card. For example, a card with a ₹2,500 fee that gives 5X rewards on your spending categories could earn you ₹8,000-₹12,000 in rewards annually. However, if your spending is below ₹2-3 lakh per year, a lifetime free card with modest rewards (1-2%) will give you better net returns since you pay no fees.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I switch from one credit card to another?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, most banks offer card upgrades or downgrades within their portfolio. For example, you can upgrade from HDFC Millennia to HDFC Regalia as your income grows. Some upgrades happen automatically based on your spending and payment history. To switch, contact your bank's customer service or check for upgrade offers in your banking app. Note that switching to a different bank requires a fresh application. Before switching, compare your current card's benefits against the new one to ensure you're genuinely getting a better deal.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Start Comparing Credit Cards Now</h3>
          <p>Use our smart comparison tool to evaluate 50+ cards side-by-side. Find the card that maximises your rewards and minimises your costs.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline">Compare Cards <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
